the student marches were the largest in china since 198687 
prodemocracy protests that resulted in hus forced resignation as 
communist party chief 
they reflected not just grief at hus death but students 
unhappiness with their living conditions and bleak career prospects 
in beijing student representatives were allowed inside the 
great hall to present their demands but emerged shortly after noon 
to say that the only response had been to go home 
police kept a low profile throughout the day and made no effort 
to stop the demonstrations 
hu who died of a heart attack saturday at age 73 is a hero of 
chinese students because he was considered a champion of the rights 
of intellectuals 
he was forced to resign in early 1987 after being accused by 
party conservatives of failing to take harsh measures against the 
prodemocracy student demonstrations of december 1986 and january 
1987 
todays beijing protest became increasingly political in nature 
as the day went on with students who carried banners and wreathes 
dedicated to hu chanting long live democracy down with 
dictatorship overthrow bureaucracy down with corruption 
students from beijing university and peoples university were 
later joined by demonstrators from qinghua university a prominent 
engineering school the nationalities university the beijing 
school of economics and other schools 
the student representatives allowed inside the great hall 
demanded repudiation of past official campaigns against liberalism 
freedom of speech and of the press more money for education and 
abolition of beijing regulations against street demonstrations 
they also demanded that senior leaders reveal their incomes and 
that the communist party reassess its ouster of hu 
march leaders placed a 15foot banner in hus honor on a 
monument in tiananmen to revolutionary heroes 
one student climbed onto the monument and demanded the 
resignation of the communist partys ruling politburo a 22member 
body the students cheered wildly and also cheered his call for a 
reassessment of hu and a government apology for past unspecified 
mistakes 
the students were surrounded by a crush of thousands of curious 
chinese workers and peasants many from outside beijing who were 
visiting tiananmen square chinas symbolic center of power and a 
main sightseeing attraction 
students sang the internationale and national anthem and 
chanted oppose dictatorship down with corruption overthrow 
bureaucracy long live democracy 
several hours after they began their protest under a hot sun 
the head of the legislatures visitors department luo xiaozha 
came out and told the students their demands are too big for one 
person to decide on right away he promised to report them to 
members of the legislatures standing committee 
beijing university vice president luo haocai urged them to 
return to campus and rest the students booed both officials 
and said they would disperse only if authorities agreed to publish 
a full account of their grievances in the staterun media and 
arrange a meeting for them with the legislative standing committee 
there was no immediate response to the new demands 
we are disappointed in deng xiaoping one peoples 
university student said of chinas senior leader who first promoted 
hu but later joined in ousting him a few years ago we supported 
him but in his later years he has made many mistakes just like 
mao tsetung 
mao leader of chinas revolution is officially acknowledged to 
have made a catastrophic mistake in allowing the 196676 cultural 
revolution a violent far lefist campaign in which thousands of 
people were killed or injured and tens of thousands had their 
careers destroyed 
the student said the 84yearold deng like mao has become 
reluctant to give up power and unwilling to brook any opposition 
jason hurpado of portland ore an english teacher at 
shanghais fudan university said the overnight demonstration in 
that city broke up shortly after students reached party 
headquarters 
