the heads of several world institutions tuesday to celebrate the 
independence of this tiny nation with a long history 
during the festivities the delegations from the soviet union 
west germany britain france austria belgium and the netherlands 
also carried out a series of oneonone discussions of eastwest 
relations and european unification officials said 
prime minister franz vranitzky of austria met with soviet 
premier nikolai ryzhkov and discussed austrias plans to ask for 
admission to the european economic community trade bloc officials 
said 
prime minister helmut kohl of west germany held an informal 
meeting with ryzhkov to talk about the visit of soviet president 
mikhail gorbachev in late spring 
during the festivities un secretary general javier perez de 
cuellar praised luxembourg as one of the most stable and 
prosperous countries in the world 
luxembourg with a population of about 370000 was declared 
independent 150 years ago after 400 years of foreign control the 
seven nations whose leaders were visiting tuesday signed the treaty 
of london in 1839 making luxembourg a grand duchy independent of 
the netherlands 
luxembourgs head of state grand duke jean also hosted an 
informal lunch tuesday for the government leaders eec commission 
president jacques delors nato secretary general manfred woerner 
and perez de cuellar 
the smallest member of the eec luxembourg borders west germany 
france and belgium lying on a crossroads of the roman and 
germanic cultures its population speaks luxembourgish a german 
dialect in addition to french and german 
it covers 998 square miles less than the area of rhode island 
