symphony no 29 in a major k 201 symphony no 39 in e flat 
major k 543 berlin philharmonic orchestra conducted by herbert 
von karajan deutsche grammaphon 
 
one way to take your mozart is like coffee light and sweet 
herbert von karajan tends more towards dark no sugar in this 
recording of two mozart symphonies no 29 one of the composers 
first great symphonies and no 39 from the final troika of 
masterpieces 
what a marvelous sleek machine the berlin philharmonic is like 
a lustrous mercedesbenz sedan it glides through symphonies the 
orchestras character is that it needs no character because its 
sheer sound is so perfect karajan the aging potentate of european 
music brings slow tempos some beautiful effects and a weighty 
intensity that occasionally borders on the plodding 
the a major symphony written by the 17yearold mozart has one 
of the most marvelous openings of his symphonies an inviting 
mysterious murmur in the strings the andante is a serenade played 
lovingly by the berlin strings karajan elicits an appropriately 
courtly dance quality to the third movement menuetto the orchestra 
brings clarity and spirit to the churning final allegro con spirito 
the highlight of the disc comes in the adagio introduction of 
the e flat symphony karajan and his forces are at their best 
bringing an expansiveness and tautness to this grandiose operatic 
section the clarinets which take the place of oboes in this 
symphony have some lovely melodies in loud passionate passages of 
the second movement karajan sometimes errs on the side of the 
plodding when trying to sound intense in another section 
successive woodwind entrances sound beautiful but aimless 
on the basis of the second movement its no surprise that the 
minuet sounds a little relentless the jaunty final allegro lacks a 
little in jaunt fast passages are clean but lifeless 
this disc is a thing of beauty but for listeners who want more 
interesting recent mozart symphonic issues consider recordings by 
sir charles mackerras and the prague chamber orcehstra on telarc 
by daniel wakin associated press writer 
